            <biogHist>
                <p>Donald MacIntyre was born to John MacIntyre, crofter, and Christina MacIntyre n√©e
                    MacIsaac. John and his wife Catherine MacIntyre lived with four children,
                    Marion, Neil, and two girls confusingly both named Catherine; it is unclear
                    whether they were both daughters. By the time of the 1871 censue, Donald
                    MacIntyre is listed as a farmer and a widower, still living with his four
                    children as well as a young nephew Robert MacIntyre (5). Donald MacIntyre died
                    of 'natural decay' in 1889 in North Lochboisdale, South Uist, listed as a
                    'pauper, formerly crofter'. </p>
                <p>Alexander Carmichael visited MacIntyre in 1877, collecting several stories.</p>
